<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="74" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1049,2006]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1049,1074]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schwarz" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[403,558,1049,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doipaensis">
<emphasis box="[403,558,1049,1074]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. doipaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from the other two 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwarz" authorityYear="1939" box="[1064,1224,1049,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1064,1224,1049,1074]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Lepidotrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. ventralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group known from 
<collectingCountry box="[559,659,1085,1110]" name="Thailand" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Thailand</collectingCountry>
as follows (see also diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer" authorityYear="2018" box="[1031,1121,1086,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[1031,1121,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above). S4 slightly concave apicomedially (
<figureCitation box="[333,410,1121,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1606,1628]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,354,1563]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,337,1584]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male metasomal sterna, ventral aspect labelled as: (A), (B), and (C) refer to L. satun n. sp. (Paratype, H.B.- GP3311), L. flavibasis (H.B.-GP3322), and L. doipaensis (H.B.-GP3183) respectively, with the number following as (1), (2), (3), and (4) refer to S4, S5, S6, and S7 respectively. All subfigures are shown at the same scale and magnification. Diagonal lines indicate the characters treated in the diagnoses." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301394/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: C1) (strongly concave and convex in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer" authorityYear="2018" box="[897,996,1122,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[897,996,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1066,1211,1121,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavibasis">
<emphasis box="[1066,1211,1121,1146]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. flavibasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
respectively). The apicosubmedial lobes of S5 pointed apically (as in 
<taxonomicName box="[727,865,1157,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavibasis">
<emphasis box="[727,865,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. flavibasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, rounded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer" authorityYear="2018" box="[1009,1099,1158,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[1009,1099,1158,1181]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), with one very long seta and often a much shorter one (two very short setae in 
<taxonomicName box="[726,865,1193,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavibasis">
<emphasis box="[726,865,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. flavibasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 4–7 setae of intermediate length in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer" authorityYear="2018" box="[1289,1380,1194,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[1289,1380,1194,1217]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). S4 gradulus touches the antecosta (
<figureCitation box="[512,583,1229,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1606,1628]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,354,1563]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,337,1584]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male metasomal sterna, ventral aspect labelled as: (A), (B), and (C) refer to L. satun n. sp. (Paratype, H.B.- GP3311), L. flavibasis (H.B.-GP3322), and L. doipaensis (H.B.-GP3183) respectively, with the number following as (1), (2), (3), and (4) refer to S4, S5, S6, and S7 respectively. All subfigures are shown at the same scale and magnification. Diagonal lines indicate the characters treated in the diagnoses." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301394/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: C1) (at least slightly separated from the antecosta in the other two species (
<figureCitation box="[159,231,1265,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1606,1628]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,354,1563]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,337,1584]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male metasomal sterna, ventral aspect labelled as: (A), (B), and (C) refer to L. satun n. sp. (Paratype, H.B.- GP3311), L. flavibasis (H.B.-GP3322), and L. doipaensis (H.B.-GP3183) respectively, with the number following as (1), (2), (3), and (4) refer to S4, S5, S6, and S7 respectively. All subfigures are shown at the same scale and magnification. Diagonal lines indicate the characters treated in the diagnoses." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301394/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: A1, B1)). S5 gradulus mostly transverse and touching antecosta medially (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1175,1265,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1606,1628]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,354,1563]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,337,1584]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male metasomal sterna, ventral aspect labelled as: (A), (B), and (C) refer to L. satun n. sp. (Paratype, H.B.- GP3311), L. flavibasis (H.B.-GP3322), and L. doipaensis (H.B.-GP3183) respectively, with the number following as (1), (2), (3), and (4) refer to S4, S5, S6, and S7 respectively. All subfigures are shown at the same scale and magnification. Diagonal lines indicate the characters treated in the diagnoses." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301394/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: C2) (not touching the gradulus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer" authorityYear="2018" box="[287,379,1302,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[287,379,1302,1325]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and doing so only briefly in 
<taxonomicName box="[720,858,1301,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavibasis">
<emphasis box="[720,858,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. flavibasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Hairs on dorsal surface of metatibia dark brown intermixed with greyish yellow ones (
<figureCitation box="[572,640,1337,1362]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[310,1276,195,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[310,1276,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male of L. doipaensis from the mountain near the type locality (Doi Suthep, Chang Khian, Chiang Mai, Thailand). (A) dorsal habitus, (B) lateral habitus, and (C) head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301404/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
: B) (only greyish yellow hairs in 
<taxonomicName box="[1012,1148,1337,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavibasis">
<emphasis box="[1012,1148,1337,1362]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. flavibasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but variably brown, dark brown or greyish yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer" authorityYear="2018" box="[476,569,1374,1397]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[476,569,1374,1397]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The gonostylus and genital capsule are also clearly different in the three species (see descriptions and 
<figureCitation box="[485,554,1409,1434]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1918,1940]" captionTargetBox="[229,1364,221,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[201,1389,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genital capsules, labelled as: (A), (B), and (C) refer to L. satun n. sp. (Paratype, H.B.-GP3311), L. flavibasis (H.B.-GP3322), and L. doipaensis (H.B.-GP3183) respectively, with the number following as (1), (2), (3), and (4) refer to dorsal, ventral, lateral, and caudal aspect respectively. All subfigures are shown at the same scale and magnification. Diagonal lines indicate the right penis valve." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301396/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The ratio of the forewing diagonal to the length of the 2nd submarginal cell separates all three species (
<tableCitation box="[454,536,1445,1470]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="16.[151,239,1012,1035]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurement of malar space length (MSL), F1 length (F1L), metatibia width (MTW), forewing diagonal (FWD), and 2nd submarginal cell (SM2L) ratios that separate L. satun n. sp., L. flavibasis, and L. doipaensis, expressed as range (Average±SD). Holotype ratios in bold." pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Table 1</tableCitation>
) and see diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer" authorityYear="2018" box="[788,879,1446,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[788,879,1446,1469]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1049,2006]" box="[199,975,1481,1506]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1481,1506]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Description.</emphasis>
As for the 
<typeStatus box="[470,568,1481,1506]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer, 2018" authorityName="Attasopa &amp; Bänziger &amp; Disayathanoowat &amp; Packer" authorityYear="2018" box="[605,696,1482,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[605,696,1482,1505]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">L. satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[703,765,1481,1506]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[703,765,1481,1506]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
except as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1049,2006]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[199,310,1518,1541]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Structure:</emphasis>
Body length 4.85–5(4.89±0.07) mm; head width 1.9–1.95 (1.93±0.02) mm; head length 1.42–1.48 (1.45±0.02) mm; eye width 0.55–0.58 (0.57±0.01) mm; gena width 0.18–0.19 (0.19±0.01) mm; interocellar distance 0.39–0.42 (0.4±0.01) mm; ocellocular distance 0.25–0.27 (0.26±0.01) mm; upper interorbital distance 1.08–1.11 (1.09±0.01) mm, lower interorbital distance 0.78–0.8 (0.79±0.005) mm; scape length excluding basal bulb 0.52–0.58 (0.55±0.02) mm, with basal bulb 0.61–0.67 (0.64±0.02) mm; 1 
<taxonomicName box="[1060,1235,1660,1685]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="flagellomere">st flagellomere</taxonomicName>
length 0.11–0.13 (0.12±0.01) mm; 2nd flagellomere length 0.2–0.22 (0.21±0.01) mm, width 0.13–0.14 (0.14±0.001) mm; 3rd shorter than 2nd; 4th longer than broad; malar space length 0.03–0.04 (0.04±0.001) mm. Forewing length 4.55– 4.76 (4.66±0.08) mm, width 1.7–1.76 (1.73±0.02) mm; forewing diagonal 1.28–1.34 (1.3±0.03) mm, length of 1 
<taxonomicName pageId="11" pageNumber="74" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="submarginal">st submarginal</taxonomicName>
cell 0.3–0.32 (0.31±0.01) mm, 2nd submarginal cell length 0.62–0.67 (0.65±0.02) mm. Metatibia length 1.61–1.73 (1.67±0.04) mm, width 0.62–0.66 (0.64±0.01) mm; metabasitarsus length 0.57–0.61 (0.59±0.02) mm, width 0.4–0.41 (0.41±0.005) mm. S4 broadly emarginate apicomedially, depth of emargination 0.15 times length of sternum medially; gradulus of S4 slightly concave medially; S5 apical margin with two long, narrow, acute lobes that delimit an emargination ~0.45 times as deep as length of sternum, emargination approximately as long as wide, submedial lobes each bearing a long, occasionally also a short, thick apical seta, S5
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301404/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" startId="12.[151,250,1971,1993]" targetBox="[310,1276,195,1951]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1971,2024]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1971,1993]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">FIGURE 7.</emphasis>
Male of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schwarz" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[365,501,1971,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doipaensis">
<emphasis box="[365,501,1971,1993]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">
L. 
<taxonomicName box="[392,501,1971,1993]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="doipaensis">doipaensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the mountain near the type locality (Doi Suthep, Chang Khian, Chiang Mai, Thailand). (A) dorsal habitus, (B) lateral habitus, and (C) head, frontal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,2035]" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">
gradulus transverse touching antecosta medially; S6 apical margin convex medially with short acute process, S7 ~twice as wide as long, apical margin weakly emarginate, bearing some distinct hairs apicomedially. Genital capsule dark brown to black except base of penis valve, apical half to 2/3 of gonostylus, and gonocoxa anteriorly which are pale brown to brown. Penis valve curved ventrally, curvature strongest on basal third to half, then almost straight, valves normally in contact with each other (exceptionally not so as in 
<figureCitation box="[1058,1128,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1918,1940]" captionTargetBox="[229,1364,221,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[201,1389,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genital capsules, labelled as: (A), (B), and (C) refer to L. satun n. sp. (Paratype, H.B.-GP3311), L. flavibasis (H.B.-GP3322), and L. doipaensis (H.B.-GP3183) respectively, with the number following as (1), (2), (3), and (4) refer to dorsal, ventral, lateral, and caudal aspect respectively. All subfigures are shown at the same scale and magnification. Diagonal lines indicate the right penis valve." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301396/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
: C1–4) and the right valve overarching the left valve. Gonostylus sclerotized basally, medial surface setose on apical ~3/7, approximately 10 times longer than wide (length 
<quantity box="[500,665,366,391]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8999999999999995" metricValueMax="7.1" metricValueMin="6.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="0.69" valueMax="0.71" valueMin="0.67">0.67–0.71 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[747,943,366,391]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.75" metricValueMax="7.3" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="0.0675" valueMax="0.073" valueMin="0.062">0.062–0.073 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,2035]" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis box="[199,493,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">Coloration of integument:</emphasis>
Head black except as follows: yellowish brown on basal bulb and extreme apex of scape (sometimes ventral surface of scape entirely yellowish brown); apical 2/3 of mandible; pedicel, and all flagellomeres dark brown. Mesosoma black except tegula; all coxae and femora black; trochanters brown; tibiae brown to black; all tarsi yellowish brown. Metasomal terga dark brown except basal depression and posterior margin of T1 yellowish brown; S1–S3 brown, except S3 laterally dark brown; S4 with large lateral dark brown spot; S5 dark brown apically, paler medially; S6 pale brown except paler on disc; S7 translucent with large lateral mark and gradulus brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,2035]" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis box="[199,340,652,677]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">Pubescence:</emphasis>
Face with plumose dense appressed white hairs; frons, vertex, lower genal area, and lower edge of mandible with long pale whitish brown hairs; longest hairs of vertex ~3/4 times as long as scape. Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum with long and very short pale whitish brown hairs, the longest hairs slightly shorter than those of vertex; mesoscutum lacking distinct band of short plumose scale-like yellow hairs; coxa, trochanter, and femora of all legs with pale brownish white hairs; all tibiae with pale brown to greyish yellow hairs, intermixed with short dark brown hairs; metatibia with short dense brownish white keirotrichia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,2035]" box="[199,694,866,891]" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis box="[199,403,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">Surface sculpture:</emphasis>
As for male 
<taxonomicName box="[550,686,866,891]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lepidotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavibasis">
<emphasis box="[550,686,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">L. flavibasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
